We were first introduced to Mbalenhle Mavimbela as Hlomu on The Wife season one, then there was Khanyi Mbau as Zandile from Zandile The Resolute, now there’s Naledi, the lover of Qhawe, who will be played by Gaisang Noge. Today marks Gaisang’s first day on the set of record-breaking and Twitter-topping Showmax Original telenovela that is inspired by Dudu Busani-Dube’s best-selling novels. Naledi is a doctor who will share a love story with one of the ladies’ favourite Zulu brothers, Qhawe Zulu, portrayed by Kwenzo Ngcobo. Like Hlomu and Zandile, Naledi will come to understand that loving one of the Zulu brothers means being understanding to their dark and tumultuous past and secrets. Gaisang well-known for her role on e.tv’s House Of Zwide, where she plays the role of Mampho, a conniving intern who would do anything to get ahead in life.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.